:H2.INDEX
:XMP.
Format&gml. &gml.INDEX  [ix=:HP1.n:eHP1.].
        (:HP1.n:eHP1.=0 -> 8)
:eXMP.
:I2 refid='gtindex' pg=major.gtindex
:I2 refid='gtih1' pg=major.gtih1
:P.
This tag may be used in the
back material of a GML document to create the formatted index.
:p.
The :hp2.ix:ehp2.
:I2 refid='gaix'.gaix
attribute selects one of the index groups (from zero through eight),
with zero being the default.
:p.
The index command line option must be specified
for the index tag to be processed.
All index tags are ignored if the option is not specified,
allowing for faster draft document creation.
